        "title": "draft: extract schema hardening slices",
        "body": "## Status\n\nThis draft is no longer a landing candidate. It is an extraction branch for the smaller hardening PRs below.\n\nThe branch is intentionally not being rebased or expanded. Current live size is 394 files / `+37298/-3990`, and GitHub reports it conflicting. Review the split PRs instead.\n\n## Landing Plan\n\n1. https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/88394 - trusted-policy fail-closed handling. Critical runtime policy safety; land first.\n2. https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/88368 - runtime/doctor active tool schema quarantine. Critical original failure path; land second.\n3. https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/88410 - Gateway MCP loopback schema hardening. Narrow gateway slice; land third.\n4. https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/88351 - provider catalog projection isolation. Keep as second-wave pending stricter review.\n5. https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/88376 - synthetic fixture-name cleanup. Do not land standalone; fold into behavior PRs where needed, then close.\n\n## Split Criteria\n\n- Keep each PR near 10 files or fewer unless one shared runtime boundary clearly requires more.\n- Prefer concrete failure modes over broad guard sweeps: pre-content assistant crash, fail-open policy behavior, malformed schema escaping runtime/provider/gateway projection, or missing doctor visibility.\n- Use synthetic fixture names such as `fuzzplugin` / `mockplugin` only.\n- Run focused tests, formatting/diff checks, autoreview, and a changed gate on each landing PR.\n\n## What This Branch Is Not\n\nThis is not a merge queue candidate, not a broad refactor proposal, and not a request to review hundreds of defensive edits. Any remaining work should be cherry-picked into fresh `gwt` branches from current `origin/main`, pruned hard, and justified against a real crash/fail-open/diagnostic gap.\n",
